body:
When personal_importRawKey is called with the same private key in a small time window, the account is registered twice.

$ curl -H "Content-Type: application/json" --data '{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"personal_importRawKey","params":["6767676767676767676767676767676767676767676767676767676767676767", ""],"id":83}' --url 127.0.0.1:8545 & curl -H "Content-Type: application/json" --data '{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"personal_importRawKey","params":["6767676767676767676767676767676767676767676767676767676767676767", ""],"id":83}' --url 127.0.0.1:8545
[1] 6012
{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":83,"result":"0x5c0fe4435ba32d64fb96ed1c37e6fc1f72641d22"}
{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":83,"result":"0x5c0fe4435ba32d64fb96ed1c37e6fc1f72641d22"}

After the above happens personal_unlockAccount calls fail.
$ curl -H "Content-Type: application/json" --data '{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"personal_unlockAccount","params":["0x5c0fe4435ba32d64fb96ed1c37e6fc1f72641d22", ""],"id":83}' --url 127.0.0.1:8545
{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":83,"error":{"code":-32000,"message":"multiple keys match address (/geth_data/keystore/UTC--2020-04-12T13-35-52.683226421Z--5c0fe4435ba32d64fb96ed1c37e6fc1f72641d22, /geth_data/keystore/UTC--2020-04-12T13-35-52.683619802Z--5c0fe4435ba32d64fb96ed1c37e6fc1f72641d22)"}}

The expected behavior is to have one of the personal_importRawKey calls fail with: "account already exists" error.
